    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rows of bead-like architectural ornaments, named for the resemblance, when seen in cross section, to prayer beads ("paternoster" referring to the "Our Father" prayer).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>成串的珠狀建築裝飾，因其橫切面看起來類似念珠而得名（串珠裝飾線條的原文(paternoster)一字意指主禱文）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
